      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty (turbulence model selection, hemolysis power-law coefficients) is acknowledged but formal model form assessment is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs (fluid properties, boundary conditions, pump geometry) must be documented with sources and uncertainty ranges.",
      "rationale": "Blood analog viscosity (3.5 mPa·s ± 0.2 mPa·s), density (1056 kg/m³ ± 5 kg/m³), inlet flow rate tolerances, and impeller geometry tolerances are all documented with measurement sources. Uncertainty quantification across these inputs has been performed using a Monte Carlo approach with 500 samples, yielding a 95% confidence interval on predicted RH of ±0.06. A note in the UQ report acknowledges that a formal sensitivity analysis to rank the dominant contributors is planned for a subsequent revision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor.",
      "rationale": "Test sample characterization beyond what is reported in the FDA experimental dataset is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
